        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(tui): clear stale pendingOptimisticUserMessage on no-active-run abort",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nClear `pendingOptimisticUserMessage` when `abortActive()` returns early with \"no active run\", preventing stale optimistic state from blocking subsequent normal prompts.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nWhen the user pressed Esc to abort, both `activeChatRunId` and `pendingChatRunId` could already be null while `pendingOptimisticUserMessage` remained `true`. The early return at the zero-run-ids guard never cleared the stale flag, so the next prompt was blocked with \"agent is busy\".\n\n## Fix\n\n1 line + comment in `src/tui/tui-session-actions.ts`:\n```typescript\nstate.pendingOptimisticUserMessage = false;\n```\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** TUI Esc abort on the zero-run-ids path leaves `pendingOptimisticUserMessage = true`, blocking the next normal prompt with \"agent is busy\" even though both `activeChatRunId` and `pendingChatRunId` are already null.\n\n**Real environment tested:** macOS 26.1 (darwin arm64), Node.js 22.22.3, running the real `createSessionActions` → `abortActive()` function via `npx tsx` against the patched source with a mock TuiBackend.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\n```bash\nnpx tsx -e '\nimport { createSessionActions } from \"./src/tui/tui-session-actions.js\";\n\nconst state = {\n  activeChatRunId: null, pendingChatRunId: null,\n  pendingOptimisticUserMessage: true,\n  sessionKey: \"test:main:main\", connected: true, ... };\n\nconst chatLog = { addSystem: () => {}, clearAll: () => {} };\nconst tui = { requestRender: () => {} };\nconst actions = createSessionActions({\n  client: { listSessions: async () => ({ sessions: [] }),\n            abortChat: async () => ({ ok: true, aborted: true }) },\n  chatLog, tui, opts: {}, state,\n  agentNames: new Map(), initialSessionInput: \"\",\n  initialSessionAgentId: null,\n  resolveSessionKey: r => r || \"test:main:main\",\n  updateHeader: () => {}, updateFooter: () => {},\n  updateAutocompleteProvider: () => {}, setActivityStatus: () => {},\n  btw: { write: () => {}, clear: () => {} },\n});\n\nconsole.log(\"Before:\", { flag: state.pendingOptimisticUserMessage });\nawait actions.abortActive();\nconsole.log(\"After:\",  { flag: state.pendingOptimisticUserMessage });\n// Before: { flag: true }\n// After:  { flag: false }  ← flag cleared on zero-run-ids path\n'\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix:**\n```\n=== Live Proof: #89506 / #86199 ===\nFix: clear pendingOptimisticUserMessage on no-active-run abort\n\nBefore abort:\n  activeChatRunId: null\n  pendingChatRunId: null\n  pendingOptimisticUserMessage: true\nAfter abort (zero run ids path):\n  pendingOptimisticUserMessage: false\n  => Flag CLEARED ✓\n\nClean state regression check:\n  Flag stays false: PASS\n\n✓ All assertions passed\n```\n\nUnit tests:\n```\nnpx vitest run src/tui/tui-session-actions.test.ts --no-color\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\n     Tests  31 passed (31)\n```\n\nTUI PTY smoke (fake-backend):\n```\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.tui-pty.config.ts\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\n     Tests  13 passed (13)\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** `abortActive()` clears `pendingOptimisticUserMessage` on the zero-run-ids path. The next normal prompt is no longer blocked.\n\n**What was not tested:** Full TUI PTY smoke with a live Gateway backend.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
